The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Good Morning
      Hello It's Thursday , July 3 , 2008                    
	Green cause    Session on Clean Development Mechanism by the Royal Thai consulate-general in Calcutta and the state department of environment, at ITC Sonar, 10am.     
	Workshop    A workshop for improving presentation skills at Hotel Hindusthan International, 10am to 6pm.     
	Dance    Bharatanatyam recital by Sumitra Chakraborty, followed by Rabindrasangeet by Tapati Bhattacharji, at EZCC, 6pm.    
	Fundraiser    Astha presents a fund-raising event at Hotel Hindusthan International, noon.    
	Theatre    Boomerang, in association with TTIS, at Gyan Manch, 7pm.    
	Art watch    Summer Show at CIMA Gallery, 2pm to 7pm.    Springs in White, an exhibition of works by contemporary Italian artists, at Rabindranath Tagore Centre, Ho Chi Minh Sarani, 11am to 6pm.     Monsoon Show, an exhibition of paintings at Academy of Fine Arts, (New South A Gallery), 3pm to 8pm.    Colourscape, a solo show by Sanjib Roy, at Kanvas Art Gallery, 3pm to 7pm.    To All Whom It May Concern, installation, paintings and video art, at Ganges Art Gallery, 11am to 7pm.    Art and Industry, an exhibition of works by artists from West Bengal, Bihar, Orissa and Jharkhand, at Gallery K2, Landsdowne Terrace, 11am to 7pm.                                                                                                                                                                 
